<P><H1 align=center>NEW LOAN AND PROPERTY – DC200</H1>
<P></P>
<P><FONT color=red><STRONG>NOTE: </STRONG>the fields shown 
in red are mandatory and must be completed to proceed</FONT>             
</P>
<P><H3>Type of Application: </H3>Pre-populated with the type 
of application you are actioning.
<P></P>
<P><H3>Type of Property: </H3>select the type of property from 
the drop-down list.
<P></P>
<P><H3>Property Description: </H3>this field is greyed out 
until the type of property field has been completed, as it depends on the type 
of property as to the options in the property description drop-down list
<P></P>
<BLOCKQUOTE style="MARGIN-RIGHT: 0px">
<P>- If House / Bungalow: options are detached, semi-detached, terraced, 
mid-terraced and end-terrace</P>
<P>- If Flat / Maisonette: options are purpose built and converted Property 
Location: select the relevant location from the drop-down list</P></BLOCKQUOTE>
<P><H3>Purchase Price / Estimated Value: </H3>this field must 
be completed to proceed. This will check that the <A HREF="HELP_MortgageTerms.asp#LTV">LTV</A> is within the <A HREF="HELP_MortgageTerms.asp#LendingCriteria">lending 
criteria</A>, and will be confirmed by the <A HREF="HELP_MortgageTerms.asp#ValuationReports">valuation report</A>
<P></P>
<P><H3>Valuation type: </H3>in this field enter the type of 
valuation required by the applicant
<P></P>
<P><H3>Family Sale / Right to Buy discount / Shared Ownership: </H3>if the answer to any of these questions is yes, click on the ‘yes’ radio 
button and the field to the right will be activated. Then complete the amount.
<P></P>
<P>Clicking on ‘<STRONG>OK’</STRONG>   leads to next screen.</P>
